# ANALYTICS TRACKING (MANAGED THROUGH GTM)
# =============================================================================
# Analytics tracking is now managed through Google Tag Manager for better
# flexibility and easier management of multiple tracking tools.
#
# What GTM can manage:
# - Google Analytics 4 (GA4) tracking
# - Facebook Pixel and Meta advertising
# - Conversion tracking pixels
# - A/B testing tools
# - Custom event tracking
# - Ecommerce tracking
#
# Benefits of GTM approach:
# - No code changes needed for new tracking tools
# - Central management of all tags
# - Advanced trigger and variable capabilities
# - Server-side tagging options
# - Better debugging and testing tools

# =============================================================================
# GOOGLE TAG MANAGER CONFIGURATION (RECOMMENDED)
# =============================================================================
# Google Tag Manager provides a unified way to manage all your tracking tags
# including Google Analytics, Facebook Pixel, conversion tracking, and more

# Google Tag Manager Container ID (required for GTM)
# Get from: Google Tag Manager > Container > Install Google Tag Manager
# Format: GTM-XXXXXXX
# This manages: all tracking codes, events, conversions centrally
PUBLIC_GTM_CONTAINER_ID=GTM-PGJB2NPL

